description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join the mental health social care team-based working across Torbay as a Social Worker on a 12 months fixed term contract working 26 hours per week.  Flexibility as to the choice of working days will be offered!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you passionate about social work and mental health?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Would you like to help shaping how we deliver services to those who need them?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is a fixed term position within a multi-disciplinary mental health community team which provides high quality mental health services across the bay to a range of adults from 18 years and onwards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be part of the newly developed mental health social care team which, whilst remaining integrated with the wider team, has a clear focus on social care and social work assessment, strength-based approach and outcome focused interventions that will support service users’ recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to carry a complex caseload and deliver a range of social work interventions, including high quality Care Act assessments and provision of services, safeguarding enquiries, Mental Capacity Assessments/Best Interest determination, proactive case management and signposting to appropriate partner agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Band 6 social worker the candidate will need to be registered with Social Work England. Applications from ASYE will also be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
